This paper deals with security analysis of programs, specifically multi-threaded programs. The paper proposes a novel model of quantitative analysis for multi-threaded programs, which is likely to fall under the category of "Computer Science and Game Theory" (cs.GT) or "Computer Science and Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses more on the practical aspects of program analysis, it is more likely to belong to the sub-category of "Programming Languages" (cs.PL) or "Logic in Computer Science" (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with the effect of observables in intermediate states along the trace, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of "Software Engineering" (cs.SE) or "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
